node.text: This Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month, we’re sharing some #Perspectives from our athletes and employees. Team athletes Nina Williams (@sheneenagins) and Ashima Shiraishi (@ashimashiraishi) covering climbing, today’s political climate, and what it means to be AAPI in the outdoors. Hosted by Hannah Abuzaineh (@my_name_is_hj ), Senior Manager of Social Impact & The Explore Fund at The North Face.

node.title: AAPI Heritage Month with Nina and Ashima

node.text: Each of us are part of a greater whole, a community that grows stronger together especially when it’s open to all. @LeannePelosi, @Jess.Kimura, @Marion_Haerty, @bigairmare, and @staywild show us just that. A unique look at these inspiring athletes that make up one hell of a portfolio. This one is for the next generation of riders carving their own paths.

node.text:
There's a beautiful circularity that occurs when your work and passions align. @margojain knows this better than anyone thanks to the support of an inner circle that inspires every climb.

A similarly passionate symmetry and creative drive inspired The North Face and @mm6maisonmargiela designers to transform our most iconic pieces in our highly-anticipated capsule for Fall 2020. See how the collaboration came full circle in this limited-edition drop, link in bio.
#MM6TheNorthFace

node.text: “We all made our way to running and the outdoors in different ways, but we all share the belief that running is about healing ourselves and healing our relationship to the land as Indigenous people. Qui’chi and I started Native Roots ATX (@nativerootsatx) because we didn’t see ourselves represented in local running and wellness groups. We fundamentally believe running is ceremony, running is life, and we run to heal ourselves and our communities in ways that honor our ancestors.”
